'''Bougie a boule''' is  [[Urology|urological]] tool used to relieve [[urethral]] obstruction.

A bougie is a long flexible rod-like instrument inserted into the urethra, esophagus, intestines, rectum or anus.  The instrument takes its name from the French word for "[[candle]]" because of a similarity in appearance as well as substance.  The instrument can be made of various substances, including waxed linen and [[gelatin]]. The gelatin permits the bougie to melt at body temperature.  The cylindrical tool can also be made of plastic, rubber or even metal.  In addition to dislodging a blockage, a bougie can also be used to widen a shaft or guide another instrument into a shaft.

The word "boule" is the French word for "ball;" a "bougie a boule" indicates that the instrument is ball- (or bulb-) tipped.



